docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:13:| OPT-P1-001 | High | Booking customer detail responses | Reuse a `select_related`/`prefetch_related` detail queryset for current-user booking retrieve and post-mutation responses so `DetailBookingSerializer` stops lazily loading company, address, payment, document, passport, arrangement, and rating relations per request. | open | Add query-count regressions for `/api/v1/bookings/<id>/`, `/api/v1/bookings/<id>/payments/`, and `/api/v1/bookings/<id>/passports/` proving the response uses a preloaded detail queryset. Source: `booking/services.py:527-548`; `booking/services.py:771-980`; `booking/serializers.py:394-519`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:168-193` |
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:14:| OPT-P1-002 | High | Partner dashboard and rating stats | Collapse partner dashboard counts and rating histograms into DB-side aggregates instead of per-bucket `.count()` loops and Python iteration over every rating row. | open | Add query-count and response-shape regressions for `/bookings/get_overall_booking_statistics/`, `/bookings/get_overall_partner_rating/`, and `/bookings/get_overall_rating_package_wise/` that prove one aggregated stats path per request. Source: `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:247-256`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:1080-1198`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:1500-1525` |
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:15:| OPT-P1-003 | High | Admin payment review queue | Replace the queue-count fan-out on the annotated `reviewable_queryset` with filtered aggregates so `/management/fetch_all_paid_bookings/` does not rerun the same join-heavy review query for each counter and summary value. | open | Add query-count regressions for `/management/fetch_all_paid_bookings/` covering default and filtered queue views, ensuring queue counts, total requests, and total amount come back from consolidated aggregates. Source: `management/approval_task.py:1246-1271` |
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:16:| OPT-P1-004 | Medium | Operator hotel catalog fallback | Stop loading and deduplicating the full `HuzHotelDetail` table in Python when the synthetic master-hotel package is missing; push dedupe/limit logic into the database or enforce canonical source data before serialization. | open | Add fallback-path coverage for `/partner/get_all_hotels_with_images/` that seeds non-catalog hotels and asserts bounded query count and bounded result size under city/search filters. Source: `partners/package_management_operator.py:1392-1429` |
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:93:## 2026-03-12 Backend Optimize Phase 0 Priority Notes
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:95:- Selected safe optimization order for the backend-optimize lane: `OPT-P1-001`, then `OPT-P1-002`, then `OPT-P1-003`, with `OPT-P1-004` kept as a fallback-path cleanup after the request-heavy booking and dashboard surfaces.
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:96:- Why `OPT-P1-001` is first: the partner lane already has a preloaded detail queryset helper, so the customer side can likely be brought onto the same pattern without changing contracts or booking-state rules.
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:97:- Why `OPT-P1-002` is next: partner stats endpoints are pure read paths, and the current implementation multiplies query load by workflow bucket count and rating volume.
docs/qa/BUG_BACKLOG.md:98:- Why `OPT-P1-003` follows: the admin payment queue is still a clear hot path, but it is admin-only and therefore slightly less urgent than customer and partner operational reads.
